m, but now i get errors in the Google Search Console that tell me that some pages have been marked as noindex in the code. Indeed, on the affected pages (my account, shopping-basket etc.) I find this in the HTML: &#8220;&lt;meta name=&#8217;robots&#8217; content=&#8217;noindex,follow&#8217; /&gt;&#8221;</p>\n<p>I found topics concerning a similar error in the html-sitemap, but that does not occur in my case because i have deactivated it. </p>\n<p>Can anyone tell me how to remove the noindex for those pages?</p>\n<p>I know that these pages not necessarily need to be indexed as they only include dynamic content tailored to the user, but Google Search Console errors drive me nuts as I&#8217;m always afraid that they will affect the ranking for the entire domain.</p>\n<p>*edit: I just checked the page itself. I still use Yoast-SEO for Meta-Titles etc. In the &#8220;Advanced&#8221;-section of Yoast SEO I can choose if the page should be indexed and it says YES. So it must be that the XML Sitemap Generator overwrites this setting somewhere.</p>\n<p>Any recommendations welcome!<br />\nThank you!</p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-12295960\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-12295960-item-12295968\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 1 month, 3 weeks ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/administratus/\" title=\"View administratus&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">administratus</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul>\n\n						\n					\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"administratus\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:26;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\